article.headline: Jacksonville 71, Florida Gulf Coast 56
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. -- Travis Cohn scored 16 points and Ayron Hardy added a double-double to help Jacksonville beat Florida Gulf Coast 71-56 on Saturday. Hardy finished with 11 points, 12 rebounds, four assists and three blocked shots for the Bulls (6-1, 2-0 Atlantic Sun Conference). Delwan Graham had 14 points and five rebounds. Jacksonville jumped out to an early lead against the Eagles, claiming a 16-2 advantage. The early spurt was capped by a 3-pointer from Cohn, who shot 3 for 5 from beyond the arc and had eight rebounds. Florida Gulf Coast answered with a 19-5 run to tie the game at 21-21 on a jumper by Marlon Rivera in the first half. But the Eagles (2-5, 0-2) never pulled ahead as Jacksonville pushed its margin to 10 points with 18:06 left in the second half on Glenn Powell's layup. Jacksonville took its largest lead at 16 points with 11:14 left.
